bitfield.description: Refer to section CAL Write DMA Real Time Traffic.

Controls if the pixel stream from the RD DMA's FIFO to the internal pipeline shall be stalled when MFlag/=0. Shall be enabled to protect real time traffic against non real time, memory to memory dataflows through CAL.

bitenum.description: Enabled. The MFlag information is propagated to the RD DMA FIFO readout control.

bitfield.description: Controls autogating of the PWRSCP clock

bitenum.description: PWRSCP clock is automatically cut when it is not needed.

bitfield.description: Refer to section CAL Write DMA Real Time Traffic

Forces the state of the CSI-3 low level protocol state machine. Intended to recover synchronization Writing 0 into this register has no effect. Reads always return 0s bit0: 0: the next OCPI transaction for this CPORT will only contain data 1: the next OCPI transaction for this CPORT will contain the CSI-3 packet header bit1~5: CPort ID (1..31)
Maximum allowed burst size for the write DMA.
Maximum number of outstanding OCP transactions = TAGCNT+1

bitfield.description: Controls stream interleaving Context #2 and #3

4 pixel from pixel processing context #0 4 pixel from pixel processing context #1 4 pixel from pixel processing context #0 4 pixel from pixel processing context #1 ...

bitfield.description: Controls stream interleaving Context #0 and #1

4 pixel from pixel processing context #0 4 pixel from pixel processing context #1 4 pixel from pixel processing context #0 4 pixel from pixel processing context #1 ...

bitfield.description: Controls PPI grouping

register.description: Controls generation of the line number event

bitfield.description: 0: Event triggered when PIX_DAT_FS TAG is received by the line number event generator 1~2^14-1: Event triggered when the LINEth occurence of the PIX_DAT_LS TAG is received by the line number event generator.

register.description: Video port control register

bitfield.description: Video port width
Vertical blanking = YBLK lines Valid range : 0 ... 63
Horizontal blanking = 8*XBLK cycles Valid range = 0..2040 cycles
Video port pixel clock = FCLK * PCLK / 2^16 Valid range: 0 .. 2^16

register.description: Video port control register

bitfield.description: Data shall be send to the video port after frame start only when (RDY_THR+1)*4 pixels are ready and the 4 PCLK cycles (require before each frame start) have been sent. This register only controls when the 1st pixels of each frame are sent. Consecutive pixels shall be sent immediately. The threshold shall be less or equal to the FIFO size.
Forces a reset of the video port FSM
Controls the behavior of the timing generator when a data tagged as PIX_DAT_FS is received.

bitenum.description: The state machine is reset on every FS

bitfield.description: Controls PCLK generation during IDLE.
Cport ID Valid range=0..(CAL_HL_HWINFO.NCPORT-1)

register.description: BYS port control register

bitfield.description: Enable/disable the BYS input port Note: the BYS output port is disabled by setting PCLK=0

bitenum.description: Disable. Ignore data received on the BYS input port.
Enable. Process data received on the BYSin port

bitfield.description: Vertical blanking = YBLK lines Valid range : 0 ... 63
Horizontal blanking = 8*XBLK cycles Valid range = 0..2040 cycles
BYSout port pixel clock = FCLK * PCLK / 2^16 Valid range: 0 .. 2^16 0 disables the BYS output port

register.description: BYS port control register

bitfield.description: Controls PCLK generation when the BYSout state machine is in the IDLE state

bitenum.description: Yes. PCLK running at the speed defined by .PCLK during IDLE.

bitfield.description: Control if data sent to the BYS output port should also be send to the DPCM encoder
BYS output port processes data received with the CPORT ID defined in this register
Cport ID used for data received from the BYSin port

register.description: Read DMA control register

bitfield.description: Controls the data rate at which data is read from the read DMA FIFO and sent to the internal processing pipeline. Data rate = FCLK * 8 * PCLK / 2^16 Bytes/s HW guarantees that data is never sent at faster rate than defined by this register. The data may be sent at slower rate when the RD DMA FIFO is empty or the processing pipeline is busy (data from OCPI has higher priority) Missed slots are not cummulated. Valid range: 0 .. 2^16
Maximum allowed number of outstanding OCP read requests minus 1 (i.e. 0xF meand up to 16 outstanding requests)

Defines a minimum cycle count between to consecutive read requests issued by the RD DMA. Used to limit the SDRAM load in memory to memory mode. The pixel rate should be controlled at video port level when data read from memory is send to the video port. Valid range = 9..4095 cycles
Enable reading of DPCM decoder initialization data from SDRAM
Start data read from memory. This bit is set by SW and automatically cleared by HW when the frame has been processed.

bitenum.description: Read DMA BUSY / it is currently fetching data from memory and sends it to the processing pipeline
Read DMA idle / ready to receive the next start trigger from SW

bitenum.description: RD DMA starts the next line when the current line finishes without waiting for other events.

RD DMA is stalled at each line end until BYSout finishes generating horizontal blanking (i.e. the state machine is in the IDLE state). register.description: Context control

bitfield.description: Number of expected lines 0: Number of lines unknown. TAG generation FSM will insert a dummy line upon reception of a FE short packet. Other values: Number of lines
Controls the data packing behavior

bitenum.description: Line mode Data is packed in between line boundaries. Line boundaries are preserved. Recomended mode for pixel data.
Frame mode Data is packed in between frame boundaries. Line boundaries are removed. Recommended mode for JPEG data.

bitfield.description: Selects which tags to use for the CAL internal pipeline

bitenum.description: Data tagged as Attributes / Embedded Data

bitfield.description: CAL internal CPort ID to use for Data
Virtual channel

DT value received over CSI-2 to use for data. 0x00 : context is disabled (don't receive data) 0x01 : filter is disabled (accept any DT) 0x02 ~ 0x0F: reserved 0x10 ~ 0x3F: receive data with Data Type field = DT
